141#define TYPE_CHECK(T, S) \
142 while (false) { \
143 *(static_cast<T* volatile*>(0)) = static_cast<S*>(0); \
144 }

177template <class T>
178class Local {
179 public:
180 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
181 template <class S>
182 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
183 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
189 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
190 }
191
195 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
196
200 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
201
202 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
203
204 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
205
212 template <class S>
213 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
214 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
215 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
216 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
217 if (b == nullptr) return false;
218 return *a == *b;
219 }
220
221 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
222 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
223 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
224 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
225 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
226 if (b == nullptr) return false;
227 return *a == *b;
228 }
229
236 template <class S>
237 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
238 return !operator==(that);
239 }
240
241 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
242 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
243 return !operator==(that);
244 }
245
251 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
252#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
253 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
254 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
255 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
256#endif
257 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
258 }
259
265 template <class S>
266 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
267 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
268 }
269
275 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
276 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
277 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
278
279 private:
280 friend class Utils;
281 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
282 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
283 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
284 template<class F> friend class Local;
285 template <class F>
286 friend class MaybeLocal;
287 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
288 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
289 friend class String;
290 friend class Object;
291 friend class Context;
292 friend class Isolate;
293 friend class Private;
294 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
295 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
296 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
297 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
298 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
299 friend class HandleScope;
300 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
301 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
302 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
303 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
304 template <class F>
305 friend class ReturnValue;
306
307 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
308 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
309 T* val_;
310};

331class MaybeLocal {

334 template <class S>
335 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
336 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
337 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
338 }
339
340 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
341
346 template <class S>
347 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
348 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
349 return !IsEmpty();
350 }
351
356 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
357
362 template <class S>
363 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
364 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
365 }

367 private:
368 T* val_;
369};

392static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
393static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
394
395template <typename T>
396class WeakCallbackInfo {
397 public:
398 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
399
400 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
401 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
402 Callback* callback)
403 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
404 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
405 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
406 }
407 }
408
409 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
410 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
411 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
412
413 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
414 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
415 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
416 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
417 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
418 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
419 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
420
421 private:
422 Isolate* isolate_;
423 T* parameter_;
424 Callback* callback_;
425 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
426};
427
428
429// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
430// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
431// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
432// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
433// possible to request a second pass callback.
434enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
435

661template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
662 public:
666 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
672 template <class S>
673 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
674 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
675 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
676 }
682 template <class S, class M2>
683 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
684 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
685 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
686 }
693 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
694 Copy(that);
695 }
696 template <class S, class M2>
697 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
698 Copy(that);
699 }
700 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
701 Copy(that);
702 return *this;
703 }
704 template <class S, class M2>
705 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
706 Copy(that);
707 return *this;
708 }
714 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
715 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
716 }
717
718 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
719 template <class S>
720 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
721#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
722 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
723 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
724 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
725#endif
726 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
727 }
728
729 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
730 template <class S>
731 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
732 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
733 }
734
735 private:
736 friend class Isolate;
737 friend class Utils;
738 template<class F> friend class Local;
739 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
740 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
741
742 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
743 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
744 template<class S, class M2>
745 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
746};

754template <class T>
755class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
756 public:
760 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
766 template <class S>
767 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
768 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
769 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
770 }
776 template <class S>
777 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
778 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
779 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
780 }
784 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
785 other.val_ = nullptr;
786 }
787 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
791 template <class S>
792 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
793 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
794 if (this != &rhs) {
795 this->Reset();
796 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
797 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
798 }
799 return *this;
800 }
804 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
805
806 /*
807 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
808 */
809 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
810
811 Global(const Global&) = delete;
812 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
813
814 private:
815 template <class F>
816 friend class ReturnValue;
817 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
818};

1006class ScriptOriginOptions {
1007 public:
1008 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1009 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1010 bool is_module = false)
1011 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1012 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1013 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1014 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1015 : flags_(flags &
1016 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1017
1018 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1019 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1020 }
1021 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1022 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1023 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1024
1025 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1026
1027 private:
1028 enum {
1029 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1030 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1031 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1032 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1033 };
1034 const int flags_;
1035};

1040class ScriptOrigin {
1041 public:
1042 V8_INLINE ScriptOrigin(
1043 Local<Value> resource_name,
1044 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset = Local<Integer>(),
1045 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset = Local<Integer>(),
1046 Local<Boolean> resource_is_shared_cross_origin = Local<Boolean>(),
1047 Local<Integer> script_id = Local<Integer>(),
1048 Local<Value> source_map_url = Local<Value>(),
1049 Local<Boolean> resource_is_opaque = Local<Boolean>(),
1050 Local<Boolean> is_wasm = Local<Boolean>(),
1051 Local<Boolean> is_module = Local<Boolean>(),
1052 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options = Local<PrimitiveArray>());
1053
1054 V8_INLINE Local<Value> ResourceName() const;
1055 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ResourceLineOffset() const;
1056 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ResourceColumnOffset() const;
1057 V8_INLINE Local<Integer> ScriptID() const;
1058 V8_INLINE Local<Value> SourceMapUrl() const;
1059 V8_INLINE Local<PrimitiveArray> HostDefinedOptions() const;
1060 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions Options() const { return options_; }
1061
1062 private:

1249class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1250 public:
1258 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1259 enum BufferPolicy {
1260 BufferNotOwned,
1261 BufferOwned
1262 };
1263
1264 CachedData()
1265 : data(nullptr),
1266 length(0),
1267 rejected(false),
1268 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1269
1270 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1271 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1272 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1273 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1274 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1275 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1276 ~CachedData();
1277 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1278 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1279 const uint8_t* data;
1280 int length;
1281 bool rejected;
1282 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1283
1284 // Prevent copying.
1285 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1286 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1287 };
1288
1292 class Source {
1293 public:

1298 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1299 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1300
1301 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1302 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1303 // alive.
1304 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1305
1306 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1307
1308 // Prevent copying.
1309 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1310 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1311

1315 Local<String> source_string;

1326 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1327 // set when calling a compile method.

1329 };

2516class V8_EXPORT String : public Name {

2579 NO_OPTIONS = 0,

2581 NO_NULL_TERMINATION = 2,
2582 PRESERVE_ONE_BYTE_NULL = 4,

2584 // unicode replacement character. Needs to be set to guarantee valid UTF-8

3750template<typename T>
3751class ReturnValue {
3752 public:
3753 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
3754 : value_(that.value_) {
3755 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
3756 }
3757 // Local setters
3758 template <typename S>
3759 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("Use Global<> instead",
3760 void Set(const Persistent<S>& handle));
3761 template <typename S>
3762 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
3763 template <typename S>
3764 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
3765 // Fast primitive setters
3766 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
3767 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
3768 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
3769 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
3770 // Fast JS primitive setters
3771 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
3772 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
3773 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
3774 // Convenience getter for Isolate
3775 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
3776
3777 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
3778 template <typename S>
3779 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
3780
3781 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
3782 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
3783 // value.
3784 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
3785
3786 private:
3787 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
3788 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;

6885struct JitCodeEvent {
6886 enum EventType {
6887 CODE_ADDED,
6888 CODE_MOVED,
6889 CODE_REMOVED,
6890 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6891 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6892 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6893 };
6894 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6895 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6896 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6897 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6898 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6899 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6900
6901 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
6902 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
6903 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
6904 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
6905 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
6906 // function.
6907 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
6908
6909 // Type of event.
6910 EventType type;
6911 CodeType code_type;
6912 // Start of the instructions.
6913 void* code_start;
6914 // Size of the instructions.
6915 size_t code_len;
6916 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6917 Local<UnboundScript> script;
6918 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6919 // code line information which is returned from the
6920 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6921 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6922 void* user_data;
6923
6924 struct name_t {
6925 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6926 // zero-terminated.
6927 const char* str;
6928 // Number of chars in str.
6929 size_t len;
6930 };
6931
6932 struct line_info_t {
6933 // PC offset
6934 size_t offset;
6935 // Code position
6936 size_t pos;
6937 // The position type.
6938 PositionType position_type;
6939 };
6940
6941 union {
6942 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6943 struct name_t name;
6944
6945 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6946 struct line_info_t line_info;
6947
6948 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6949 void* new_code_start;
6950 };
6951
6952 Isolate* isolate;
6953};
6954
6960enum RAILMode {
6961 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6962 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6963 // Throughput may be throttled.
6964 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6965 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6966 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6967 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6968 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6969 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6970 // in this mode.
6971 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6972 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6973 // turn off latency optimizations.
6974 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6975};
6976
6980enum JitCodeEventOptions {
6981 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
6982 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
6983 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
6984};
6985
6986
6992typedef void (*JitCodeEventHandler)(const JitCodeEvent* event);

8716template <class T>
8717class Maybe {
8718 public:
8719 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8720 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8721
8725 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8726
8731 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
8732 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8733 }
8734
8739 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8740 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8741 return IsJust();
8742 }
8743
8748 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8749 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8750 return value_;
8751 }
8752
8757 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8758 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8759 }
8760
8761 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8762 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8763 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8764 }
8765
8766 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8767 return !operator==(other);
8768 }
8769
8770 private:
8771 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8772 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8773
8774 bool has_value_;
8775 T value_;
8776
8777 template <class U>
8778 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8779 template <class U>
8780 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8781};
8782
8783template <class T>
8784inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
8785 return Maybe<T>();
8786}
8787
8788template <class T>
8789inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
8790 return Maybe<T>(t);
8791}
8792
8793// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
8794template <>
8795class Maybe<void> {
8796 public:
8797 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
8798 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
8799
8800 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8801 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
8802 }
8803
8804 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8805 return !operator==(other);
8806 }
8807
8808 private:
8809 struct JustTag {};
8810
8811 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
8812 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
8813
8814 bool is_valid_;
8815
8816 template <class U>
8817 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8818 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
8819};
8820
8821inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

9453
9454template <class T>
9455Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
9456 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
9457 T* that_ptr = that;
9458 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
9459 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
9460 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
9461}

9467 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9468 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
9469 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
9470}

9472template <class T>
9473Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
9474 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
9475 // need to open a handle.
9476 return Local<T>(val_);
9477}

9498template <class T>
9499T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
9500 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
9501 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
9502 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
9503 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
9504 p));
9505}

9508template <class T, class M>
9509template <class S, class M2>
9510void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
9511 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
9512 this->Reset();
9513 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
9514 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
9515 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyPersistent(p));
9516 M::Copy(that, this);
9517}

9519template <class T>
9520bool PersistentBase<T>::IsIndependent() const {
9521 typedef internal::Internals I;
9522 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9523 return I::GetNodeFlag(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_),
9524 I::kNodeIsIndependentShift);
9525}

9527template <class T>
9528bool PersistentBase<T>::IsNearDeath() const {
9529 typedef internal::Internals I;
9530 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9531 uint8_t node_state =
9532 I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_));
9533 return node_state == I::kNodeStateIsNearDeathValue ||
9534 node_state == I::kNodeStateIsPendingValue;
9535}

9540 typedef internal::Internals I;
9541 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
9542 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
9543 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
9544}

9550 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_));
9551 val_ = nullptr;
9552}

9690template<typename T>
9691void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
9692 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9693 typedef internal::Internals I;
9694 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
9695 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
9696 return;
9697 }
9698 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
9699}
9700
9701template<typename T>
9702void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
9703 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
9704 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
9705 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
9706 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
9707 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
9708 return;
9709 }
9710 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
9711}
9712
9713template<typename T>
9714void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
9715 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
9716 typedef internal::Internals I;
9717 int root_index;
9718 if (value) {
9719 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
9720 } else {
9721 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
9722 }
9723 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
9724}

9731}

9755 typedef internal::Internals I;
9756 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
9757 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
9758 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
9759}

9943
9944Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
9945#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS) && !defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
9946 typedef internal::Address A;
9947 typedef internal::Internals I;
9948 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
9949 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9950 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9951 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9952 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9953 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9954 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
9955 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSizeForEmbedderFields +
9956 (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
9957 A value = I::ReadTaggedAnyField(obj, offset);
9958 internal::Isolate* isolate =
9959 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
9960 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
9961 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
9962 }
9963#endif
9964 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
9965}
9966
9967
9968void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
9969#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS) && !defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
9970 typedef internal::Address A;
9971 typedef internal::Internals I;
9972 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
9973 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
9974 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
9975 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
9976 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
9977 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
9978 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
9979 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSizeForEmbedderFields +
9980 (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
9981 return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
9982 }
9983#endif
9984 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
9985}

10003
10004String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
10005 typedef internal::Address A;
10006 typedef internal::Internals I;
10007 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10008
10009 ExternalStringResource* result;
10010 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
10011 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10012 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
10013 } else {
10014 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
10015 }
10016#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10017 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
10018#endif
10019 return result;
10020}
10021
10022
10023String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
10024 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
10025 typedef internal::Address A;
10026 typedef internal::Internals I;
10027 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10028 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
10029 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
10030 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
10031 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
10032 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
10033 void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10034 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
10035 } else {
10036 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
10037 }
10038#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10039 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
10040#endif
10041 return resource;
10042}

10052
10053bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
10054 typedef internal::Address A;
10055 typedef internal::Internals I;
10056 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10057 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10058 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10059 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
10060}

10063bool Value::IsNull() const {
10064#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10065 return FullIsNull();
10066#else
10067 return QuickIsNull();
10068#endif
10069}
10070
10071bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
10072 typedef internal::Address A;
10073 typedef internal::Internals I;
10074 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10075 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10076 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10077 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
10078}
10079
10080bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
10081#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10082 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
10083#else
10084 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
10085#endif
10086}
10087
10088bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
10089 typedef internal::Address A;
10090 typedef internal::Internals I;
10091 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10092 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10093 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
10094 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
10095 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
10096}

10101#else

10106bool Value::QuickIsString() const {
10107 typedef internal::Address A;

10109 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10110 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
10111 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);

10542
10543int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10544 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10545 typedef internal::Internals I;
10546 constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10547 int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10548 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10549 int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10550 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10551 int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10552 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10553 I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10554
10555 const int64_t amount = *external_memory + change_in_bytes;
10556 *external_memory = amount;
10557
10558 int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10559 *external_memory - *external_memory_at_last_mc;
10560 // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
10561 // external memory increased.
10562 if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10563 CheckMemoryPressure();
10564 }
10565
10566 if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10567 const int64_t lower_limit = *external_memory_limit + change_in_bytes;
10568 if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit)
10569 *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
10570 } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10571 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10572 }
10573 return *external_memory;
10574}

10576Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10577#if !defined(V8_ENABLE_CHECKS) && !defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS)
10578 typedef internal::Address A;
10579 typedef internal::Internals I;
10580 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
10581 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
10582 A* result =
10583 HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, I::ReadEmbedderData<A>(this, index));
10584 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10585#else
10586 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10587#endif
10588}
